 Foreign nationals along with local residents embark on campaign to end xenophobic attacks Picture: Hendrick Mphande
About 150 foreign nationals together with local residents embarked on a door to door crime awareness campaign in Motherwell on Saturday.
The initiative is aimed at curbing a spate of xenophobic attacks and other crimes in Wells Estate.
Sweetness Pullen, Director of the Eastern Cape Refugee Centre, said they have decided to visit nine wards in Motherwell including crime hot spots to highlight the plight of foreign nationals and lawlessness in general.
“Our message is simple. Know your neighbour.
“This is just the beginning of our campaign to eradicate crime such as robbery and xenophobia,” Pullen said.
The campaign is expected to end with a soccer tournament between the locals and foreign nationals.

